IRS990.MissionDesc: TO SPONSOR HIGH SCHOOL EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES AND PROGRAMS
IRS990.Desc: THE BRANDON VALLEY BOOSTER CLUB WAS FORMED TO ASSIST AND SUPPORT THE BRANDON VALLEY SCHOOL DISTRICT, THE STUDENTS, AND THE COACHES THROUGH COORDINATION OF PARENT SUPPORT FOR ALL THE EXTRACURRICULAR PROGRAMS, PROVIDING FINANCIAL SUPPORT FOR NEEDED EQUIPMENT AND SUPPLES, PROVIDING EDUCATION SCHOLARSHIPS TO SENIOR STUDENTS, AND ORGANIZING RECOGNITION PROGRAMS FOR ALL EXTRACURRICULAR PROGRAMS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH SPORT (SANCTIONED OR SPONSORED BY THE BVHS) HAS A TRUST AND AGENCY ACCOUNT THAT IS HELD BY THE BOOSTER CLUB. THESE ACCOUNTS ARE SUBSETS OF THE BOOSTER CLUB'S CHECKING ACCOUNT. ALL ACCOUNTING ACTIVITY IS TRACKED IN THE FINANCIAL SOFTWARE OF THE BOOSTER CLUB TREASURER. THE BOOSTER CLUB IS ONLY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ADMINISTRATIVE ACTIVITES ON BEHALF OF THE TRUST AND AGENCY ACCOUNTS.

RecipientTable.PurposeOfGrantTxt: SUPPORT FOR HIGH SCHOOL ACTIVITIES & EXTRACURRICULAR

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOOSTER CLUB PAID OUT (16) SCHOLARSHIPS. THE TOP TWO CANDIDATES RECEIVED THE $1,000 BV BOOSTER CLUB - PAT VAN WHYE MEMORIAL SCHOLARSHIP AWARD. THE NEXT TOP TWO CANDIDATES RECEIVED THE $750 ARCHITECTURE INCORPORATED SCHOLARSHIP AWARD. THE REMAINING TWELVE WINNERS RECEIVED $500 SCHOLARSHIPS. ELIGIBLE CANDIDATES MUST HAVE PARTICIPATED IN ATHLETICS AS AN ATHLETE, MANAGER, OR TRAINING DURING HIS/HER SENIOR YEAR AND COMPLETED THE ENTIRE SEASON. ELIGIBLE CANDIDATES MUST HAVE A GRADE POINT AVERAGE OF AT LEAST 3.5 AND MUST BE ATTENDING A POST-SECONDARY SCHOOL IN THE FALL FOLLOWING GRADUATION.

THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL CONSIST OF THE PRESIDENT, VICE PRESIDENT, SECRETARY, TREASURER AND IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT. THE IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT IS NOT REQUIRED TO HAVE A STUDENT IN BRANDON VALLEY HIGH SCHOOL WHEN SERVING IN THIS CAPACITY. THE BVHS ATHLETIC DIRECTOR SHALL BE AN EX-OFFICIO MEMBER OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS SHALL DESIGNATE ANY ADDITIONAL BOARD MEMBERS TO SERVE ON THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME AFTER THE ANNUAL MEETING OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. VACANCIES IN THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE FILLED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. DURING THE INTERVALS BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL POSSESS AND MAY EXERCISE ALL THE POWERS AND FUNCTIONS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IN THE MANAGEMENT AND DIRECTION OF AFFAIRS OF THE BOOSTER CLUB IN ALL CASES IN WHICH SPECIFIC DIRECTION SHALL NOT HAVE BEEN GIVEN BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. IN ADDITION, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MAY POSSESS AND EXERCISE SUCH POWERS AND RESPONSIBILITIES AS DELEGATED TO IT BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BY RESOLUTION. ALL ACTIONS OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE REPORTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AT ITS MEETING NEXT SUCCEEDING SUCH ACTION.
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS INCLUDE NUMEROUS MARRIED COUPLES AND FAMILY RELATIONSHIPS.
THE CLUB HAS APPROXIMATELY 48 DIRECTORS WHO ARE ALSO BOOSTER CLUB MEMBERS. VARYING LEVELS OF MEMBERSHIP EXIST, AND LEVELS ARE DEPENDENT ON DOLLAR AMOUNT PAID.
MEETING MINUTES OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ARE INCLUDED IN THE MINUTES OF THE FULL BOARD MEETING AS ALL EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ACTION IS PROVIDED TO BOARD MEMBERS DURING THE FULL BOARD MEETING.
A COPY OF FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED. THE FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE DRAFT PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

ALL BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE COVERED BY THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR IDENTIFYING AND REPORTING SUCH CONFLICTS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MAY REVIEW POTENTIAL CONFLICTS. ANYONE WITH CONFLICTS IS ASKED TO RETIRE FROM THE ROOM WHILE THE MEETING IS HELD.
THE BYLAWS ARE POSTED ON THE BOOSTER CLUB WEBSITE AND ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
